76561198038963412,Recommended,244070,7821303,"Posted: 29 November, 2013",all,C0untzer0,"8.5/10 great little casual.Don't be thrown by the ""Sid Meier's"" part. This is a game that you can pick up and run with in a coffee break, but will still draw you in for the long sessions. Originally made for mobile devices, it's short sweet and simple. this is reflected in the price, so it's easy to buy with no regrets. The Graphics aren't amazing, but they don't leave your eyes bleeding. Things kinda look like the things they should look like, and the style reminded me of ""WINGS"" waaay back in my Amiga days. The controls are fairly straightforward, and the icons make it obvious. (a twisty arrow beside you means ""roll this way"" an arrow curling upwards means ""Climb"" etc) so there is no need for a long training mission, just enough to check you can click and tell how to shoot the enemy. The different factions and their planes are given special commands or abilities which fit in without intruding (some turn faster, some have better guns, etc)If you see it on sale, remember that you can download it faster than you read this review. I guarantee it'll make a train journey fly past, (especially in 2-player hotseat mode) or make a nice break between ""serious"" games on your rig at home."
76561198039222800,Recommended,244070,32727087,Posted: 24 June,all,kingts,"There's a definite wall at times attached to strategy games. Sid Meier's Ace Patrol sidesteps these stigmas to a fault, Designed for iOS devices originally, Ace Patrol is a dogfighting game set in WWI. With a series of manuevers to intense air combat is engaged over a battlefield of hexagonal grids. Using simple mouse commands,  players execute everything from strafing to swooping dives, hard banking, the Immelman turn and other expert maneuvers and that is it. My Pros and ConsPROSA: Simple easy tutorial, very streamlined tactic, you can name pilots, promote, and simply follow the action on different skill levels.B: Atfer a while it is more planning than executing as you start to recongnize patterns in the enemy.C: You feel like an ACE at times because of the simple dynamics of Ace Patrol. Even my 5 year old got it.D:  It does not try to do too much. Missions are straight forward and easy to pick upE: The look is simple, colors to customize your planes, and good solid sound effects and graphics. even if they are old school.CONSA; Its positive is it's negative. Not much of a challenge beyond the missions and goals. There is no strategy features like building up your squadron size, no real story mode of the pilots you select. It is too simple for its own goodB: The enemy is too redundant and not fun enough. Since you stay fighter pilots, you don't get to have fun being a bomber, or torpedo plane, execute full mission goals, like an actual stragey WW1. This is just flying and shooting, which may turn off players.C: The game quit on me a few times and then reloaded on its own, with the quick save, you never lose your place. However, annoyingD: Like many other Firaxis missed an opportunity to have a true ww1 strategy game. They could have doubled down and make a real neat WWI strategy turn based game like PTO, Instead chose one aspect and streamlined that. Their lossOVERALL: Ace Patrol does its job, perhaps too well to simplify things. I finished the game in several hours in easy mode, BUT found it more fun on higher level skills. Keep that in mind. Again, go to the discussion, see VIDEO of gameplay before you buy. For the price or a few dollars. Worth adding for some simple funOVERALL: 3 out of 5 stars"
