,Recommended,244070,12162474,"Posted: 20 September, 2014",all,Vita ζ,"A excellent turn-based strategy game.The focus is on the aerial combat of World War 1 and in the game, you control a squadron of 4 pilots.You can select between playing as the US, Britain, France and Germany which affects the planes you start with.Like mentioned, the gameplay is turn-based and you play through a number of Operations, which are sets of 6 missions and you have a choice of 3 missions at each interval, all with differing objectives which eventually lead up a final mission, usually destroying a large Zeppelin of the enemy force.The game has a lot of customizing to it, with nameable pilots, colourable planes and of course, new planes that become available gradually. Your pilots are customizeable in the way of promotions and special medals, which allow them to learn new moves like Power maneauvers, Slide, Roll as well as a number of special Ace skills.It's a fairly short game but i still found it very entertaining."
