76561198119331877,Recommended,244070,17456913,"Posted: 9 August, 2015",all,dved002,"Interesting little game, it's a turn-based tactical game, very basic in its design - set in Europe during WW1, you can choose to play as the British, French, Americans or Germans.In terms of challenge - On easy there is very little skill involve - simply get behind your opposition, not in front of them, and continue to shoot them until you've defeated them. As you increase the difficulty the challenge really does ramp up and you will need to plan what manueveres to upgrade your pilots with and understand how and when to use them, it becomes like a chess game.The set up of the game is that your participate in 5 battles, and there are 5 engagements within each battle. They are literally just randomly generated engagements based off the same 4 engagement types - Combat Air Patrol, Search & Destroy, Recon or Escort. However you can choose from one of 3 engagements offered, this means you can choose to challenge yourself or avoid doing that one engagement type that you've become bored of. There are also some random bonus or ""Challenge"" missions which get thrown in too.Overall if you like turn-based tactical or even if you're just a fan of WW1 it could be and interesting way to waste a few hours."
